<p>I have model many to many relation like. I want to relate <strong>State</strong> and <strong>Category</strong> through pivot table CategoryNews.</p>  <p>Category model</p>  <pre><code>class Category extends Model {     public function news() {          return $this-&gt;belongsToMany('App\News');      }  } </code></pre>  <p>News model</p>  <pre><code>class News extends Model     {          public function categories()         {             return $this-&gt;belongsToMany('App\Category');         }         public function state()         {             return $this-&gt;belongsTo('App\State');         } } </code></pre>  <p>and the State model</p>  <pre><code>class State extends Model {     public function news() {          return $this-&gt;hasMany('App\News');      }   } </code></pre>  <p>I want to select the news related to the state where cat_type=2(from category table) i tried</p>  <pre><code>$slide_news = State::whereHas('news.categories',function($query){ $query-&gt;where('categories.cat_type',2);})                      -&gt;with(array('news'=&gt;function($query){                      $query-&gt;orderBy('created_at', 'desc');}                    ))-&gt;where('id',$id)-&gt;first(); </code></pre>  <p>but the cat_type filter is not working. I also tried hasManyThrough but i don't know how to implement it with Pivot Table Please help</p>